---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import TrustStrip from '../components/TrustStrip.astro';
import CTABlock from '../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { BASE } from '../data/business';

const title = 'About Sorn Handyman Services | Fraser & Aidan, father & son, East Ayrshire';
const description = '20+ years on the tools (Fraser) plus a qualified mechanical engineer & plumber (Aidan). Family-run, insured, 24/7 across East Ayrshire. Learn how we work.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/about/">
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[{ name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` }, { name: 'About' }]} />
  <article class="container-x py-12 max-w-3xl prose-sorn">
    <span class="eyebrow">Who we are</span>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-serif text-5xl font-black text-navy-900">Father and son. One van. One phone number. Always on.</h1>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg">
      Sorn Handyman Services is Fraser and Aidan — father and son, one van, the KA5 postcode on our doors. We work out of Sorn village and across the Ayr and Irvine valleys — Mauchline, Cumnock, Catrine, Auchinleck, Galston, Kilmarnock, Ayr, Troon, Prestwick, Irvine, Maybole — day, night and weekend.
    </p>

    <h2>Fraser — 20+ years on the tools</h2>
    <p>
      Fraser has been a tradesman for over two decades. Joinery is his first trade — you can tell by the way he eases a door into a cottage frame that was cut before central heating was invented — but he’s picked up every next-door skill the job demands: tiling, harling, slating, slabbing, decking and the hundred small repairs that sit between trades.
    </p>

    <h2>Aidan — qualified mechanical engineer & plumber</h2>
    <p>
      Aidan came up through the engineering side — qualified mechanical engineer and qualified plumber. He handles the water end of the work, the flat-pack builds that need a steady Allen key, and the paperwork that keeps the business running. If there’s a written quote in your inbox, Aidan wrote it; if the kitchen tap stopped dripping at 3am, Aidan was the one with the wrench.
    </p>

    <h2>Why 24/7?</h2>
    <p>
      Because a burst flexi hose at 11pm isn’t waiting until Monday, and a cracked pane on Christmas Eve isn’t a January job. When we started this we made a simple deal: one of us answers every call. The number on the side of the van rings a real phone — and one of us has it.
    </p>
    <p>
      Non-urgent call at 2am? We book you in for first light and go back to sleep. Flooding kitchen at 2am? We’re in the van. Either way you get a real voice and a plan in about thirty seconds.
    </p>

    <h2>How we quote</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Photo over WhatsApp — <strong>ballpark back within the hour</strong>.</li>
      <li>Site visit and a <strong>written, fixed-price quote</strong> for anything over £200.</li>
      <li>No call-out fee. We only start charging once we’re on the tools.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Insured and accountable</h2>
    <p>
      £2m public liability, certificate on request. Written quotes, bank transfer or card, no cash pressure. A line-by-line invoice on completion and a photo-log of the finished job for anything big enough to stand back from.
    </p>

    <h2>Local, not hypothetical</h2>
    <p>
      We live here. Our kids walk the same streets, our parents drink in the same pubs, our vans park on the same High Street. A handyman who lives four miles away and cares what the postie and the pub landlord think is a different animal to one being dispatched through an app.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you’ve a job, call <a href="tel:+447900255876">07900 255876</a> or message WhatsApp — whoever’s closer will be there first.
    </p>
  </article>
  <TrustStrip />
  <CTABlock heading="Any job. Any hour. One call." />
</BaseLayout>
